                  </persName>
            . I live in York-terrace, Kingsland-road - Mr. William Barlow has a duck-pond in a field which he rents. About the middle of June I saw the prisoner with a man named Ware, who was convicted here; they got a penny-loaf, and they threw the bread to the ducks, and when they came near, they caught them, and put them into their pockets.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-318-person2296">
                  GEORGE 
                  BARTRAN
               <interp inst="t18310908-318-person2296" type="surname" value="BARTRAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-318-person2296" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-318-person2296" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Mr. Barlow. I was in his field - I saw the prisoner and the other lad come and entice the ducks with the bread - they went away - the prisoner escaped at that time, but was taken afterwards.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-318-person2297">
